The paper deals with distributed constraint optimization problems, which are a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The algorithm proposed in the paper is an asynchronous search algorithm, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses bounded-error approximation mechanisms, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
